## 2. Changelog
Check for changelog and get recent commits:
```bash
echo "=== Existing Changelog ===" && \
find . -maxdepth 1 -iname "changelog*" -o -iname "history*" -o -iname "releases*" && \
echo -e "\n=== Recent Commits ===" && \
git log --oneline --no-merges -20
```

If missing, create CHANGELOG.md:
- Use Keep a Changelog format (https://keepachangelog.com/)
- Organize by version with sections: Added, Changed, Deprecated, Removed, Fixed, Security
- Start with current version and work backwards

If changelog exists but outdated, get commits since last update:
```bash
git log --oneline --no-merges --since="$(git log -1 --format=%ai -- CHANGELOG.md)"
```

## 3. README
Check for README and analyze structure:
```bash
echo "=== README Files ===" && \
find . -maxdepth 1 -iname "readme*" && \
echo -e "\n=== README Sections (if exists) ===" && \
(test -f README.md && rg "^#{1,3} " README.md || true)
```

README must include:
- **Project description**: What it does, why it exists
- **Installation**: Clear installation instructions
- **Quick start**: Minimal working example
- **Usage**: Key features and examples
- **Requirements**: Dependencies, supported versions
- **Documentation**: Link to full docs if available
- **License**: "Apache 2.0 - see LICENSE file"
- **LaunchDarkly Labs disclaimer**: 
  ```
  This repository is maintained by LaunchDarkly Labs. While we try to keep it 
  up to date, it is not officially supported by LaunchDarkly. For officially 
  supported SDKs and tools, visit https://launchdarkly.com
  ```

Check if README has badges (add if missing):
- License badge: `[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-Apache_2.0-blue.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/Apache-2.0)`
- Build status (if CI exists)
- Version/release badge

## 4. Repository Metadata

### Naming Conventions
Follow LaunchDarkly naming patterns (lowercase with hyphens):

**SDKs:**
- Client SDKs: `[platform]-client-sdk` (e.g., `angular-client-sdk`)
- Server SDKs: `[language]-server-sdk` 
- Framework-specific: `[framework]-client-sdk` (e.g., `react-client-sdk`)

**SDK Components/Integrations:**
- Data stores: `[language]-server-sdk-[store]-[client]`
- Libraries: `[language]-[function]`
- Shared code: `[language]-sdk-common`

**Tools & Integrations:**
- CLI tools: `[tool-name]` or `ld-[name]`
- IDE extensions: `ld-[editor]`
- Provider/Plugin: `[platform]-[type]-launchdarkly`

**GitHub Actions:**
- Action repos: `[action-name]` (e.g., `find-code-references-in-pull-request`)
- Add topics: `github-action`, `github-actions`, `actions` (all three)

**Examples:**
- Pattern: `hello-[language/framework]` or `hello-[language]-[feature]`

